&lt;p&gt;Back to School Night&amp;nbsp;Schedule from Dr. Pecoraro:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;September 10, 2012&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dear Families,&lt;br /&gt;Welcome back to the 2012-2013 school year! We are excited about welcoming you to our Back-to-School Night on Thursday, 9/13. Due to calendar constraints this year, we are planning to&amp;nbsp;have a one night Pre-School, K-5 event. We anticipate that this plan will be easier for parents&amp;nbsp;who have children at different grade levels, negating the necessity of coming to LCS on two&amp;nbsp;consecutive nights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Many of you know how challenging parking is at LCS. Therefore, we will be using our parking&amp;nbsp;lot as well as the Liberty Corner Presbyterian Church lot. The church has been very generous&amp;nbsp;about sharing their space with us, so please be sure to adhere to their parking specifications and&amp;nbsp;not park in the Children&amp;rsquo;s Corner spaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The evening will begin promptly in the gym at 6:00 for K-2 parents and at 8:00 for 3-5 parents. The schedule is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 30px;&quot;&gt;5:30-6-PTO dues collection, cafeteria&lt;br /&gt;6-6:15 - K-2 parents assemble in the gym&lt;br /&gt;6:30-7 - Grades K-2 Classroom Presentations&lt;br /&gt;7-7:15 - Specialists Visitations for K-2 parents/ PTO Dues Collection both in cafeteria&lt;br /&gt;7:15-8 - Pre-School presentation/Transition time-K-2 parents leave, 3-5 parents arrive&lt;br /&gt;8-8:30 - Grades 3-5 Classroom Presentations&lt;br /&gt;8:30-8:45 - Grades 3-5 Specialists Visitations in Cafeteria/PTO Dues Collection&lt;br /&gt;8:45-9:15 - Parents Invited for Refreshments/PTO Dues Collection&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, for your convenience, our Specialists (Mr. Peluso, Mrs. Beadle, Ms. Bynoe, Mr.&amp;nbsp;Mullarkey, Mr. Henthorn, Mr. Fico) will be located in the cafeteria for visits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to an enjoyable and informative evening.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sincerely,&lt;br /&gt;Dr. Pecoraro, Principal&lt;br /&gt;Mr. Oliver, Assistant Principal&lt;/p&gt;
